# Playtest notes / backlog

## Done
- [x] tsc/build/lint CI gate â€” `verify (no browser)` now runs `npm run build` (`tsc --noEmit && vite build`) right after `npm ci`. Prompted by the TypeScript 5.9.3â†’7.0.2 dependabot bump (#4): the new DOM lib types widened `HTMLElement.hidden` to `boolean | "until-found"`, breaking a `classList.toggle` call in `src/ui/fileTree.ts` â€” Vitest (esbuild-transpiled, no type-check) and the Playwright job (dev server, no build) both stayed green and the PR merged clean, so the break only surfaced on the next local `npm run build`. Fixed by coercing to `Boolean(open)` at the call site; CI now catches this class of break before merge.
- [x] enhance weapon "sprites", they cause eyecancer, and they weren't aligned to the actual position ammo is fired from â€” the viewmodel was drawn 2% right of true screen-center (`cx = w * 0.52 + bobX`) while `RaycasterEngine.fire()`'s tracer/flame-stream have always launched from a fixed, simulation-adjacent point at exact screen-bottom-center; first attempt wrongly moved the tracer to chase the gun's drawn position, but the correct direction is the reverse â€” the gun is the cosmetic element, so it's the one that should conform to the fixed shot origin. Fixed by recentering the viewmodel (`WEAPON_CENTER_BIAS` 0.52 â†’ 0.5 in `viewmodel.ts`) instead of touching `effects.ts`/`engine.ts`'s tracer origin at all. Every weapon's Canvas-2D silhouette also got a polish pass (dark outline strokes + a bottom-shadow band to match the existing top-highlight, giving flat fills some bevel) while keeping the existing primitive-shape style rather than a full redesign
- [x] enhance soundfx, esp. weapon fire â€” every weapon's fire sound was previously the same shared `audio.playShoot()` blip; each of the 7 weapons now has its own procedurally-synthesized voice dispatched off `weapon.viewKind` (`src/engine/audio.ts`): pistol keeps the original snap, shotgun layers a distorted thump with a filtered noise burst, gdb gets a cheap high-pitched tick, ghidra gets a rising launch whoosh (distinct from its existing impact boom), Friday Hotfix gets a continuously-blended rumble+hiss jet, the knife/Toolchain get an airy whoosh / gritty revving buzz respectively â€” gdb/Friday Hotfix/Toolchain's rapid auto-fire retriggers add a small `Math.random()` pitch jitter so a burst doesn't sound clone-stamped
- [x] flamethrower must burn 2.5x gas considering its dmg â€” Friday Hotfix's `ammoPerShot` raised from `1` to `2.5` (`src/engine/weapons.ts`), same flat cost every other weapon pays otherwise; HUD's gas readout now floors the value (`src/engine/hud.ts`) since the pool can land on a half-unit
- [x] antialiasing for wall edges â€” the top/bottom silhouette against ceiling/floor is now sub-pixel blended per column instead of floored to whole pixels (which caused the classic raycaster "staircase" jaggies), by proportionally alpha-blending the one boundary row at each edge with whatever's already painted underneath (`renderScene` in `src/engine/raycaster.ts`); zBuffer/sprite-occlusion resolution is untouched; verified headlessly by bundling `raycaster.ts` and rendering a synthetic wall in Playwright/Chromium, confirming the boundary pixel is a proportional blend of wall and background color [Task 71]
- [x] console hints keep coming when game is paused, spamming away previous output â€” engine now fires an `onFreezeChange` edge event on the paused/lore-frozen â†” running transition, which the console sidebar uses to suspend its ambient hint timer while frozen (resumes once unpaused)
