- [x] option for gorelevel, which controls the amount of blood effects. normal/default is current state, add "no gore", "more gore" and "extreme gore" options on top. â€” a Gore dropdown in the sidebar (None/Normal/More/Extreme = 0x/1x/3x/10x) persisted to localStorage, scaling blood-particle count, rendered size, and how long a landed particle lingers as a floor stain (a genuinely new concept â€” previously every particle vanished under a second regardless of whether it had landed) [Task 30]. Follow-up: Extreme (10x) reads as over-the-top in practice â€” hidden from the dropdown for now behind `EXTREME_GORE_ENABLED = false` in effects.ts (same disable-behind-a-flag pattern as `DECORATIONS_ENABLED`); a previously-saved "extreme" preference downgrades to "more" instead. Also found and fixed a real, previously-shipped bug while verifying this: `GORE_KEY`'s `const` was declared below the point where `loadGoreLevel()` was first called, so every read hit its temporal-dead-zone, threw, got silently swallowed by an empty `catch`, and the Gore setting never actually persisted across a reload â€” it always silently reset to Normal regardless of what was saved. Second follow-up (re-enabling Extreme, 2026-07-17): root-caused the "over-the-top"/"mountain of blood" complaint â€” `renderBlood`'s particle size formula (`tilePx * 0.05 * sizeMultiplier`) had no upper clamp, and `tilePx` (pixels per world tile) grows unbounded as depth approaches the close-range render cutoff, so a single old-extreme (10x) point-blank particle could render at ~800px, nearly twice the real gameplay canvas's own height â€” that's the literal mountain, not particle accumulation. Fixed three ways: retuned `GORE_MULTIPLIERS.extreme` to `{count:16, size:4, stainDuration:4}` (size/stainDuration cut well below a naive 10x, since size scales rendered area quadratically and old extreme had countĂ—sizeĂ—stainDuration all maxed together, a ~1000x "visual mass" jump over `more`'s 27x; count bumped from an initial 10 to 16 once the size fix made more particles safe to add back â€” user-requested follow-up, same day); added an unconditional hard pixel clamp in `renderBlood` (`BLOOD_MAX_SIZE_FRACTION = 0.06`, 6% of canvas height â€” applies to every gore tier, not just extreme, since `more` was technically unclamped too); added a hard cap on live particle count (`MAX_BLOOD_PARTICLES = 300`, FIFO-evict-oldest in `spawnBlood`) as defense-in-depth against the newly-shipped Multi/Ultra Kill feature chaining several enemies' hits within a few seconds. `EXTREME_GORE_ENABLED` flipped back to `true`. Verified: full Vitest suite (1543 tests) at 100% coverage including new clamp/eviction tests in `effects.test.ts` and rewritten/added `main.test.ts` cases for the now-enabled dropdown option and a mocked-disabled-flag branch-coverage case; live check driving the real `renderBlood`/`spawnBlood`/`updateBlood` functions against a real canvas in a real browser (headless Playwright's pointer-lock support turned out too unreliable for genuine in-game combat navigation â€” confirmed via `getPlayerState()` showing near-zero movement/shots fired despite held input) confirmed a point-blank multi-hit burst renders as small uniform clamped squares, and a simulated 6-kill chain produces a dense-but-bounded spatter pattern confined to a modest fraction of the screen, not a solid mass climbing toward enemy-sprite height
