- [x] multikill score bonus, sfx and a text-gfx in the canvas (ut like) (starting at 3 kills in 3sec, becomes an ultrakill yielding even more points at 6 kills in 6 secs) â€” a rolling-window kill-streak check in `engine.ts`'s new `registerKillForStreak()` (called from `damageEnemy` right after each kill) compares the in-window kill count before/after adding the new kill, so each tier fires exactly once per streak: 3 kills within 3s triggers a "MULTI KILL!" banner (amber, 300 bonus points), 6 kills within 6s an "ULTRA KILL!" banner instead (red/bigger, 750 bonus points) â€” Ultra is checked first since 6-in-6 implies 3-in-3 already fired earlier in the same streak. New procedurally-synthesized SFX pair (`playMultiKill`/`playUltraKill` in `audio.ts`, modeled on the existing `playExplosion`/`playRocketExplosion` "smaller vs. bigger" precedent â€” Ultra adds two more arpeggio notes plus a noise-burst layer). New `drawKillStreakToast` in `hud.ts` â€” a bold, UT-style banner in the upper third of the screen, frame-counted fade like the existing cheat-activation toast, sized/colored by tier. `scoring.ts`'s `computeScore` gained a flat `multikillBonus` field (count Ă— per-tier bonus, same pattern as the existing lore/secret-room bonuses). A temporary `demo-campaign/stage99_multikill_playtest.c` level (13 trivial low-complexity functions, ~97 enemies) was added for manually playtesting/hearing it in a real browser (audio can't be verified by any automated/headless run by design â€” `AudioManager.isSilenced()` mutes all SFX under browser automation on purpose) â€” user confirmed it works (2026-07-17), level removed afterward.
