- [x] SEO optimize the page for dist build / hosted gameplay â€” static-meta SEO (no SSR/prerendering, out of scope â€” pure client-side SPA): `meta description`, canonical link, Open Graph + Twitter Card tags, a minimal schema.org `VideoGame` JSON-LD block, and a one-line `<noscript>` notice added to `index.html`; `public/robots.txt` + `public/sitemap.xml` (single-URL, this is a one-page app); `package.json` gained `description`/`homepage`. Canonical URL: `https://codeenstein3d.mcdope.org/` (intended hosting domain â€” no live deploy exists yet). New `public/og-image.png` (1200x630, opaque) generated from the same CODE logo source as the favicons, tagline text overlaid. See `doc/dev/decisions.md`'s SEO entry for the full detail.
- [x] balancing telemetry should track score reached â€” score was already threaded through the engine's `getTelemetrySnapshot()` (`stats.score`, `RaycasterEngine.buildStats()`) and per-level averaged in `scripts/run-balancing-telemetry.mjs`'s `aggregateLevelRuntime`, but nothing surfaced *the score a run actually ends at* â€” the per-level figure pools every level's own end score together (mixing early-level low scores with late-level cumulative ones), which answers "what does a typical level-end score look like," not "how far did a run's score climb by the time it stopped." Added `computeFinalScoreReached(qualifyingRuns)`: takes each qualifying run's *last* level snapshot's `score` (already the correct running-campaign-total semantics per `EngineStats.score`'s doc comment) and runs it through the same `spread(..., "mean")` helper every other per-run stat (`weaponAcquisitionRate`, etc.) already uses â€” new `finalScoreReached` field on `buildComboOutput`'s per-combo (profileĂ—difficulty) output, alongside `qualifyingRunCount`/`weaponAcquisitionRate`.
- [x] Forced weapon unlock for MP at the 4th level, 8th for rocket launcher (in a campaign only) â€” a 1-based campaign level counter (persisted in the campaign save) force-adds gdb/ghidra to `ownedWeapons` once reached, regardless of whether an Elite ever dropped them; never removes anything, so an already-looted weapon is unaffected. Only advances via the auto-chain (`advanceToNextLevel`), not manual sidebar picks [Task 31]
