- [x] score penalties hit to hard, feels like the score is decreasing all the time while playing. seen it happen that i had less score after an level than before it. â€” two real bugs found in `scoring.ts`/`engine.ts`, both fixed. (1) Health loss was scored twice: `healthBonus` already scaled 0â†’500 with remaining health fraction, but a separate `hpMalus` also scaled 0â†’200 *against the same fraction* and got subtracted on top â€” full-to-zero health swung the total by 700 points off one input instead of 500. Removed `hpMalus` entirely; `healthBonus` alone now covers it. (2) `RaycasterEngine` is a fresh instance every level, and `EngineCarryover` only ever forwarded health/armor/bullets/rockets/weapon â€” never kill points, lore bonus, or the flat 750pt map-completion bonus â€” so the live score collapsed back to near-zero at every level transition instead of continuing to grow; that's the direct cause of "less score after a level than before it." `EngineCarryover` gained a `priorScore` field (score banked from every level already cleared), threaded through both real carryover-construction sites (`advanceToNextLevel`'s auto-chain and the "Continue Run" resume handler) and added into `buildStats()`'s live score, so the HUD number is now a genuine running campaign total that only resets on a fresh run. Verified against the real `computeScore`/`RaycasterEngine` in headless Chromium: full-to-zero health now costs exactly 500 points (was 700); a synthetic 2-level run showed the second level's score at its very first frame already sitting at the first level's carried-over total plus its own fresh bonuses, never dropping [Task 47]
