s the run's own line off-center across the room's width instead of always dead-centering it, so consecutive rooms actually look different from each other. More importantly, a new `breakUpRoomSightline` walls off one interior column/row of the room with a single guaranteed 1-tile gap positioned away from the entry/exit line (the same "solid wall, one gap" technique `carveLabyrinth`'s `divide` already uses for guaranteed connectivity) â€” without it, the room was just a wider stretch of the same straight corridor, since flooding a rect on top of an already-carved straight run does nothing to interrupt the sightline still running directly through its middle. Hit a real, systematic bug while verifying this: `enemyPositions`' first-enemy-at-room-center pick frequently landed exactly on the new baffle tile for these small odd-dimensioned rooms, and `clearCriticalTiles` (which force-clears the tile under every enemy's position to guarantee it's floor) then silently punched the baffle back open â€” in a first verification pass this defeated the sightline fix on the majority of rooms, not a rare edge case. Fixed with a new `nearestFloorInRect` that snaps any Edge Case enemy spawn position landing on a wall tile to the nearest actual floor tile within its room (BFS-bounded to the room's own footprint) before `clearCriticalTiles` ever sees it. Verified against the real generator: a Node+esbuild harness confirmed real shape variety (9+ distinct widthĂ—height combinations) and, across repeated seeds on small/typical/medium-sized synthetic files, the intended entry-exit sightline is broken in every room checked (0 failures) â€” a residual ~15% "still straight" rate persists only in an artificially dense worst-case stress scenario (30+ entities packed onto a maxed-out map), traced to coincidental adjacency from a *different*, unrelated corridor touching the room's other wall (a pre-existing property of this generator's parse-order-chained corridor connectivity, not a failure of the baffle itself, which the room's own entry/exit line was confirmed broken in every case checked)

