run to death correctly shows exactly the 1 real entry afterward, not mixed with or reverting to the 3 shipped ones. Every one of the 10 generation runs that produced a valid entry cleared exactly `main.c` (level 1) and died on `stage02_bootstrap.sh` (level 2) â€” consistent rather than varied, but within the accepted scope: `recordHighscore` accepts any non-cheated run with `levelsCleared >= 1`, the bot was never intended to reliably clear all 17 levels (especially the multi-Elite `stage17_the_monolith.php` finale), and "run several times, keep the best" was the explicit ask rather than a guaranteed full clear. `defaultHighscore.ts`'s own doc comment (and this entry) flag that it must be regenerated if `demo-campaign/`'s source files ever change, since a stale `astHash` makes `startReplay` refuse playback â€” a doc-comment warning, not an automated staleness checker, since this is a manually-triggered, infrequent regeneration step [Task 80].
