- [x] code optimization/reuse, complexity reduction etc â€” four rounds of engine/parser perf and dedup work, in commit order. **Task 82** (`sprites.ts`/`engine.ts`/`main.ts`/`astUtils.ts` + adapters) â€” a shotgun/MP shot was re-projecting every living enemy and every visible mine from scratch per pellet; new `projectLivingEnemies`/`projectVisibleMines` snapshot the projection once per shot, and `findTargetInProjections`/`findMineInProjections` hit-test against that snapshot (still re-checking `.alive` per pellet, since an earlier pellet in the same shot can kill/destroy the target mid-loop) â€” `findTargetAtColumn`/`findMineAtColumn` stay as thin single-hit wrappers for the aim reticle. Also switched `main.ts`'s background `computeCodebaseStats` scan from a fixed every-20-files yield to a `CODEBASE_STATS_TIME_BUDGET_MS` (6ms) wall-clock budget (bounds worst-case stall regardless of how large/slow any one file is, instead of letting a burst of unusually large files run unbounded between yields), and had the C/PHP/generic adapters share one `descendantsOfType` comment-node walk between `extractLargeComments`/`findCommentedOutCodeBlocks` instead of each re-walking the tree (`astUtils.ts`'s new `...FromNodes` variants). **Task 83** (`ammo.ts`/`lootApply.ts`/`enemyAi.ts`/`sprites.ts`, pure dedup/no behavior change) â€” four parallel ammo fields plus ~7 repeated 4-way branches collapsed into one `Record<AmmoType, number>` + per-pool metadata table; `applyLoot`/`grantOrTopUpWeapon`/`dropEliteLoot` moved out of the 300+-line `engine.ts` into their own `lootApply.ts` behind a narrow `LootContext`; the elite/edge-case damage and speed ladders and the two near-identical per-axis wall-slide implementations in `enemyAi.ts` collapsed into shared helpers; `projectiles.ts`/`rockets.ts`'s near-duplicate orb-billboard collectors (including a duplicated private clamp) unified into one palette-parameterized `collectOrbBillboards` in `sprites.ts`. **Task 84** (`enemyAi.ts`/`rockets.ts`, new `spatialGrid.ts`) â€” an already-aggroed enemy no longer re-ray-marches line of sight every frame just to redo an idempotent write, and the aggro-check/ranged-fire-check now share one lazily-memoized per-enemy-per-frame LOS result instead of computing it twice; rockets got a new tile-bucketed `EnemySpatialGrid` (rebuilt only on frames with a rocket in flight) replacing a full-enemy-array scan per rocket for proximity and per blast for AoE â€” kill order (and the seeded loot rolls it drives) is preserved via ascending array-index order. **Task 85** (new `pathField.ts`) â€” the biggest remaining scaling cost on enemy-dense maps: every chasing enemy previously flood-filled its own fresh windowed BFS every frame; replaced with one shared full-map BFS distance field rooted at the player's tile (flat `Int32Array`, reflooded only when the player crosses a tile boundary or the grid mutates, tracked via a new engine `gridVersion` counter), which every enemy now just descends with the same neighbor order/strict-decrease rule as before (the old Â±(aggro+2)-tile window check is kept so distant sticky-aggroed enemies still steer straight rather than gaining cross-map pathing). SIM-AFFECTING: the old per-enemy flood was window-clipped, so a chasing enemy can now occasionally find a route the old code couldn't see â€” shipped default highscores/replays regenerated (`npm run generate:default-highscore`) and re-verified to match. All four rounds kept `tsc --noEmit`/`verify:campaign`/`verify:campaign:playthrough` green; Tasks 82-84 confirmed behavior-identical via a same-session replay trajectory digest, Task 85 confirmed replay-*compatible* (not identical â€” see SIM-AFFECTING above) after regeneration. Directly targets the magento `check_copyright_pr.php` shooting-performance report (below): the described symptom â€” a large function count (many enemies) plus repeated per-frame/per-shot O(enemies) work while firing â€” is exactly what Tasks 82/84/85 remove, though not indepe