- [x] github repo loads should ignore folders like "test", "Test", "tests" and so on â€” `IGNORED_DIRECTORIES` (`src/fs/workspace.ts`) now also skips `test`/`tests`/`__tests__`, and matching is case-insensitive across the board (via a new `isIgnoredDirectoryName` helper) instead of an exact-string `Set.has`, so `Test`/`Tests`/`__Tests__` etc. are caught too. Shared by both the local File System Access walker and the GitHub tree builder, same as the rest of the skip-list. Follow-up: a dedicated test *directory* doesn't cover ecosystems (including this repo's own) that colocate tests right next to the source they cover â€” added `isIgnoredFileName`, a regex-based filter for `foo.test.ts`/`foo.spec.js`, `test_foo.py`/`foo_test.go`, `foo_spec.rb`, and `FooTest.java`/`FooTests.cs`-style suffixes, applied to individual files in both walkers. The Java/C#-style suffix match is deliberately case-sensitive on the capital "Test" so real words ending in "test" (`Contest.java`, `Latest.php`) aren't caught.

